  "response": "Charlie Chaplin was not a Gypsy, also known as Roma or Romani. He was born in London, England, on April 16, 1889, to parents who were both entertainers. His father, Charles Chaplin Sr., was a vocalist and actor, and his mother, Hannah Chaplin (stage name Lily Harley), was a singer and actress. There has been speculation and rumors about Chaplin's heritage, including claims that he might have had Romani ancestry, but there is no concrete evidence to support these claims. Chaplin himself never confirmed any Romani heritage, and his known ancestry is primarily English and Irish.",
